<blockquote>
<p>Had you redacted the article like that, I would have called you out for poor expungement. You've apparently just removed all the actual content from those sections, though given that I cannot decipher them in their original form I can't be certain.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>No. Read what I wrote. First, I'm aware that that's poor expungement, and said so myself: "Redacting that stuff would be clumsy". My point is that the sections don't really have any further content written either way (aside from a clue about the real-life identity of the scp), but the terminology is present because <em>that's how a scientist would write this.</em></p>
